{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #357: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $1\\leq a_1<\\cdots <a_k\\leq n$ be integers such that all sums of the shape $\\sum_{u\\leq i\\leq v}a_i$ are distinct. Let $f(n)$ be the maximal such $k$.\n\nHow does $f(n)$ grow? Is $f(n)=o(n)$? Current best: If $g(n)$ is the maximal $k$ such that there are $1\\leq a_1,\\ldots,a_k\\leq n$ with all consecutive sums distinct (i.e. we drop the monotonicity assumption in the definition of $f$) then Hegyv\\'{a}ri \\cite{He86} has proved that\\[\\left(\\frac{1}{3}+o(1)\\right) n\\leq g(n)\\leq \\left(\\frac{2}{3}+o(1)\\right)n.\\]The upper bound of Coppersmith and Phillips in [867] implies\\[g(n) \\leq \\left(\\frac{2}{3}-\\frac{1}{512}+o(1)\\right)n.\\]A similar question can be asked if we replace strict monotonicity with weak monotonicity (i.e. Prize: no. OEIS: A364132, A364153. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_2a6e52cff05fd35b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos357.erdos_357.variants.monotone.parts.ii.littleO_version https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos357.erdos_357.variants.monotone.parts.ii.littleO_version.","id":"vf_5ff17d56bb0ecec1","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"attempted via frontier 'sidon/B2' (transfer_strength=partial) -> no_progress","claimed_status":"draft","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_5ab012bb2fe34702","kind":"dead_end","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"sidon/B2","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_5ab012bb2fe34702","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":1,"banked_attempt_count":1,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1